2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the design goals for flash memory systems, which involves the use of efficient data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the properties of flash memories and their design goals, which are related to hardware architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the trade-off between "payload" and "coding efficiency" in flash memory systems, which is related to system design and control. 
5. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - Flash memories are commonly used in embedded systems, and the paper's focus on the design goals for flash memory systems suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
